subject: p19748558
History: Dyspnea and cough, right-sided back pain.
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest demonstrate heterogeneous opacities in the left mid lung. Similar opacities are also seen in the right lung base. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax. Hilar and mediastinal silhouettes are unremarkable. Heart size is normal. No pulmonary edema.
Impression: Multifocal pneumonia. Follow-up exam following resolution of the symptoms is recommended.
